entry.title: Introduce LRUCache for SharedDictionaryStorage
entry.content:
Currently, a SharedDictionaryStorage is kept alive as long as there is a

CorsURLLoaderFactory object that matches its

SharedDictionaryIsolationKey. This means that once CorsURLLoaderFactory

is deleted, Chromium needs to load the metadata from the database again.

For example, if a site has a cross origin iframe in every pages, a page

navigation in the site always triggers the database read for the cross

origin iframe. This is not good for performance.



To mitigate this problem, this CL introduces a LRUCache in

SharedDictionaryManager to keep SharedDictionaryStorages. The cached

SharedDictionaryStorage will be evicted when MemoryPressure is detected.



Bug: 1413922

entry.content:
Follow up to crrev.com/c/4632098



Ideally, the view should not be observing the pref directly. This CL

makes OmniboxEditModel observe that pref and notify OmniboxPopupView

to update itself. OmniboxPopupView in turn updates OmniboxResultView

and OmniboxHeaderView and its own layout. For that to happen, this CL

refactors OmniboxHeaderView which is internal to OmniboxRowView into

its own file and provides an accessor to it like for OmniboxResultView.



Also moves setting and reading the header toggle state to the

OmniboxController.

entry.title: webauthn: don't prelink in work profiles.
entry.content:
When Chrome is running in an Android work profile, it would still

publish prelinking information. This can cause Chrome on the desktop to

select that instance of Chrome to connect to for hybrid transactions,

but from inside of a work profile, only work profile passkeys can be

used. Thus this change suppresses publishing any pre-linking information

from inside a work profile.

entry.title: [ SavedTabGroups ] Fix bug for synced devices displaying wrong tab order
entry.content:
When a SavedTab is reordered in the Tabstrip we would only notify sync of the tab that was moved. This lead to inconsistency across devices as they would move the tab to the correct position but fail to update the positions of the other tabs that were not moved. This happens when a user moves multiple tabs in quick succession (Think of the ball and cups magic trick).



Additionally, every time we reorder a group in the bookmarks bar, all data about the groups including the tabs were synced. While this method will ensure ordering it is also highly expensive as we only need to keep track of the group reorders and not the tabs in this case.



Fix:

- Add a new observer function SavedTabGroupTabsReorderedLocally

- Remove tab notifications when a SavedTabGroup is reordered

- Notify sync of all the tab positions when a SavedTab is reordered in the Tabstrip

entry.title: [Win] Don't adjust window position when the browser window is snapped.
entry.content:
Users can snap browser windows to the desktop and the user can

manage app's position/size via resize grip. The position/size

of snapped window shouldn't be changed during WM_WINDOWPOSCHANGING.

If the position or size is changed, the window pops out and resize

grip can't be used anymore.



This change skips window position adjustment when the window is

snapped.
